    "result": {
      "result": "{\"meta\": null, \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/Users/REDACTED/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_student_database_english_talent_67526/20101701_Isabella_Davis/recommendation_letter.txt:\\nTo the Selection Committee,\\n\\nI am writing to enthusiastically recommend Isabella Davis (Student ID: 20101701) for your consideration. As Isabella Davis's academic advisor and professor for the past year, I have had the privilege of observing their growth and development as a student and individual.\\n\\nIsabella Davis has consistently demonstrated exceptional academic performance, maintaining high grades while taking challenging coursework. Their analytical abilities and attention to detail are particularly impressive. They have shown a remarkable ability to grasp complex concepts quickly and apply them effectively in practical situations.\\n\\nWhat truly distinguishes Isabella Davis is their intellectual curiosity and commitment to excellence. They are always eager to learn more and often go beyond the required coursework to explore topics in greater depth. Their research skills and ability to synthesize information from various sources are outstanding.\\n\\nIn terms of character, Isabella Davis is reliable, ethical, and demonstrates strong moral values. They are respected by their peers and have shown excellent teamwork and communication skills.\\n\\nBased on my comprehensive evaluation, I would rate Isabella Davis's overall performance as S grade level. I am confident that Isabella Davis will continue to excel in their future academic and professional endeavors.\\n\\nI give Isabella Davis my highest recommendation without reservation.\\n\\nSincerely,\\nProf. Jones\\nAssociate Professor\\nSchool of Information Technology\\nNovember 19, 2024\\n\\n---\\n/Users/REDACTED/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_student_database_english_talent_67526/20102572_Michael_Taylor/recommendation_letter.txt:\\nTo Whom It May Concern,\\n\\nI am writing this letter of recommendation for Michael Taylor (Student ID: 20102572), who has been my student for the past academic year. I have had the pleasure of teaching Michael Taylor in several advanced courses and have been consistently impressed by their academic performance and personal character.\\n\\nMichael Taylor has demonstrated exceptional academic abilities throughout their time in my classes. They consistently achieved high grades and showed a deep understanding of the course material. Their analytical thinking and problem-solving skills are particularly noteworthy.\\n\\nIn terms of personal qualities, Michael Taylor is highly motivated, responsible, and shows great initiative in their studies. They are always well-prepared for class discussions and contribute meaningfully to group projects. Their ability to work effectively both independently and as part of a team makes them an ideal candidate for further academic pursuits.\\n\\nBased on my observations and Michael Taylor's academic record, I would rate their overall performance as C grade level. I have no hesitation in giving Michael Taylor my highest recommendation for any academic or professional opportunity they may pursue.\\n\\nIf you require any additional information about Michael Taylor, please do not hesitate to contact me.\\n\\nSincerely,\\nProfessor Smith\\nDepartment of Computer Science\\nUniversity of Technology\\nMay 30, 2025\\n\\n---\\n/Users/REDACTED/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_student_database_english_talent_67526/20104653_Sophia_Brown/recommendation_letter.txt:\\nTo the Selection Committee,\\n\\nI am writing to enthusiastically recommend Sophia Brown (Student ID: 20104653) for your consideration. As Sophia Brown's academic advisor and professor for the past year, I have had the privilege of observing their growth and development as a student and indiv